{
  "texts": [
    "In particular, although predictive coding networks include recurrent connections, they generate the same prediction for a given input (when inputs are constrained but outputs are not; Fig. 2a) as standard feedforward ANNs if their weights are set to corresponding values 12, 14.",
    "Therefore, loss is the same function of weights in both models, so direct minimization of loss with gradient descent in predictive coding networks (which is not their natural way of training) would produce the same weight changes as backpropagation in ANNs.",
    "Hence, comparing predictive coding networks and backpropagation enables isolation of the effects of the learning algorithm (prospective configuration versus direct minimization of loss as in backpropagation).",
    "In Fig. 3a, we compare the activity of output neurons in the exam ple in Fig.",
    "1 between backpropagation and prospective configuration."
  ]
}